    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis issue was reported in Neovide https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/1745\r\n\r\nSome users want to make the cursor color the inverse of the text, but the cursor only supports one type of \"inverse\", the inverse of foreground and background color, which we interpret as the inverse of the default foreground and background colors in Neovide.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI think there should be a new style, `inversetext` (or similar) to support the other type of inverse colors. \r\n\r\nThe alternative is to have a global option in the Gui implementation that controls the behaviour but I think a dedicated option would be better.",
